pageContext.claim: “The whistle blower comes out with a totally phony report on my phone call, but they never thought I'd release it. So they were gonna be okay. ‘Eight times, quid pro quo,’ except it was no time.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump appears to be mixing up the whistleblower's Aug. 12 complaint with a news report. The Wall Street Journal reported that Trump allegedly pressed Ukrainian officials eight times for investigations that would help his 2020 reelection campaign. The whistleblower's complaint makes different assertions and has been corroborated by Trump's own remarks and other witnesses and evidence.
